# Simple Authentication using MERN

A secure authentication system built with the **MERN Stack (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js)**.  
It provides user **registration**, **login**, and **logout** functionality, protected by **JWT (JSON Web Tokens)** for secure session management.

---

## Features

- User registration with validation  
- User login and logout  
- Protected routes using JWT  
- Passwords securely hashed before saving to database  
- Integrated frontend (React) and backend (Node + Express)  
- MongoDB for database management  

---

## Tech Stack

**Frontend:** React, Axios, React Router  
**Backend:** Node.js, Express.js, JWT, bcrypt  
**Database:** MongoDB (Mongoose)  

---

## Installation & Setup

### Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/authentication.git
cd authentication

### Install dependecies
cd server
npm install
cd client
npm install

### Environment 
Create a .env file inside the server folder and add:

PORT=5000
MONGO_URL=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key

### Run the application

cd client
npm start
cd server
node index.js